The paper deals with the decidability of the regular emptiness problem of a class of automata, which is a typical topic in formal language theory and automata theory. The paper also mentions the use of automata in program verification, which suggests a connection to formal methods and software engineering. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science), followed by cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.PL (Programming Languages), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
